\par \tab }{\b 1. Messages from office to vending - }{This option is if the managers want to send a message from the office to the vending when returning recounts.  Th
is could be any sort of message like, "Spree are short" or "Recount Twist 'n go again, stupid." or "There aren't 45 M&Ms in a display case."  This is used to improve communication between the office and vending stand and could potentially speed up the cou
nts process.
\par \tab }{\b 2. Inputting the values of the counts into the Radiant system - }{This will be some button that inputs the values automatically, all this will consist of three different buttons: "Move up", "Move down", and "Input Next".  Overall, this will most
ly eliminate the need for entering the values via the keyboard.  It's hard to explain when not implemented, so I'll leave it at that.
\par \tab }{\b 3. Timer to keep track of amount of time spent on counts -}{ This will keep track of the amount of time counts spent in the
 office and in the vending stand.  This is just a little feature to add that is not all that important, but would be an interesting addition to the group.
